The paper discusses the detection of fake news on social media, which involves analyzing news content, social context, and dynamic information. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Computers and Society (cs.CY), Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Among these, cs.SI and cs.CL are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the study of social media and natural language processing, respectively.
